value.0: There's nothing for us to discuss. If you know what's good for you, you'll stay far away from this part of the woods.
Oh, you're the one who rescued Revat's mother. So what do you want? I'm sorry, I'm in a foul temper today.
Excellent. Bring me the troll Chieftain's head and I will pay you with the gold I made from the current expedition.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> You're kidding, right? I don't even smell the stench of caverns on you. Bring me back his head as proof, or I'll find someone who is actually capable.

<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Excellent. It is only a matter of time until a new troll chieftain resurfaces. But at least the threat is eliminated and my brother can rest in peace... for now. Here is your gold, as promised.
As a matter of fact, yes. I am still haunted by the image of my brother being torn to shreds by those trolls who ambushed us on our expedition.
I will take that off your hands and burn it with pleasure. I wish I had more gold to pay you, but here is what I can offer.
Very well. Good luck to you in the future. I will be here, monitoring the area to see if a new troll chieftain arises.
I thank you for vanquishing the troll chieftain. However, I'm sure another will rise one day. Perhaps I can count on you, when that day comes. For they must be wiped out!
<StartCheck>[Bluff]</Start> I have already slain the troll chieftain.
